## Sources and Texts

The primary documents recounting the Alessian Revolt include the *Songs of Pelinal*, a series of fragmentary texts describing the exploits of the Divine Knight, and the *Adabal-a*, memoirs attributed to Morihaus himself. These texts, though partly mythologized, constitute the oldest sources on this foundational event.

The Alessian Revolt endures in Tamriel's collective memory as the moment when humanity passed from slavery to sovereignty — an act of liberation whose consequences, political, religious, and metaphysical, continue to shape the world millennia later.
